  "text": "Once the first author had analysed the whole sample, an experienced serving investigation professional examined 15% of the interviews (N =11) at random concerning question types, EDMs, evidence weight, and interview outcomes. Table 1 shows that in much of the interviewer analysis high levels of Kappa coefficiency were achieved (using recognised metrics of concordance - [CITATION_1] . Occasional disagreement was found between the raters in regard to whether some closed questions were either appropriate or inappropriate resulting in more moderate Kappa observer agreement values. Strong levels of inter-rater agreement were also found when assessing the various evidence disclosure modes, questioning strategies, interview skills, evidence weight, and interview outcomes. ",
